---
source: tests/conformance/query_v1_matrix.rs
assertion: ee.query.v1 query-file output and budget controls are observable and not silent no-ops
schema:
  query_file: ee.query.v1
  response: ee.response.v1
contracts:
  - output.explain=true is accepted and reports that JSON packs already include selection audits and per-item why details
  - output.explain rejects non-boolean values with stable machine errors
  - budget.maxResults constrains candidate count through the query-file execution path
  - maxResults appears in the request echo or degradation metadata so users can verify it was applied
  - JSON stdout remains the response envelope and diagnostics stay off stdout
evidence:
  - tests/conformance/query_v1_matrix.rs::matrix_output_explain_true
  - tests/conformance/query_v1_matrix.rs::matrix_budget_max_results
  - src/cli/mod.rs::output_from_document
  - src/cli/mod.rs::budget_from_document
  - eidetic_engine_cli-93jo
